structured.title: Family Prepares Chicken Dinner
structured.overview: The household members discuss timing and preparation for a meal involving chicken, potatoes, and carrots. There is a brief disagreement about how long the chicken was left and whether it needed to rest for an hour, along with coordination on when to put potatoes in the oven versus using an air fryer. One person explains they finished chopping and getting items into the oven while waiting, to avoid food sitting idle. Near the end, the user asks Tara if she has heard back from Helen at the center regarding some blue items, and Tara begins to respond before the transcript ends.
